FBIS4-58521 "drnes087_m_94011" FBIS-NES-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 JORDAN Egypt's Sadqi Arrives for Meetings Egypt's Sadqi Arrives for Meetings JN0405200194 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 1900 GMT 4 May 94 JN0405200194 Amman Jordan Television Network English BFN [From the "News at Ten" program] [Text] Egyptian Prime Minister 'Atif Sadqi flew to Amman this evening to attend meetings of the Joint Jordanian-Egyptian Committee on cooperation. He was greeted by Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali. The Egyptian prime minister said he hoped the committee meetings would strengthen cooperation between the two countries. [Begin Sidqi recording] We hope by renewing the meetings, this joint committee, the Jordanian-Egyptian Higher Committee, would strengthen the relations between our two countries for the benefit not only for Egypt or Jordan but for all the Arab people. [end recording] "News at Ten" asked Prime Minister al-Majali about his impressions following today's signing of the PLO-Israeli agreement in Cairo. [Begin al-Majali recording] I am a very optimistic man, all my life, so I am not going to change this time, and I think I am still optimistic and I always look forward to the implementation. And what I felt today, there is a real spirit of having honest implementation. [end recording]
